mode_python
Tim Tyler and Dietmar Schwertberger's Python file colouring mode.
For more details there is a help file available.

PYTHON_FLAGSTOGGLE <word> (ZapPython - Tim Tyler/Dietmar Schwertberger)
This has the same syntax as the WFORMAT_TOGGLE command.  It ticks menu
entries if it is attached to them.

PYTHON_SETDELAY <byte> (ZapPython - Tim Tyler/Dietmar Schwertberger)
Sets the delay in centiseconds used by bracket matching in the Python mode.

PYTHON_SETINDENT <byte> (ZapPython - Tim Tyler/Dietmar Schwertberger)
Sets the size of the indentation in characters used in the Python mode.
